article.headline: N.J. Tech 65, Wagner 56
article.story: NEW YORK -- Chris Flores scored 25 points to lead New Jersey Institute of Technology to a 65-56 win over Wagner on Monday night. Isaiah Wilkerson added 19 points and five assists for the Highlanders (4-9), who snapped a four-game losing streak. Both Wilkerson and Flores added six rebounds apiece. The score was close for much of the game, but NJIT used a 10-2 run to take a 55-43 lead with 4:29 remaining. Wilkerson scored eight points during the run. Wagner would get no closer than within five points the rest of the way. Wagner (2-11) was paced by Chris Martin, who finished with 18 points and six steals. Michael Orock added 11 points and 10 rebounds. The Highlanders outrebounded Wagner 45-35. It was the second meeting of the two teams this season, as NJIT also beat Wagner 56-51 on Nov. 24.
